Package org.apache.jena.sparql.resultset

Class TextOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.jena.sparql.resultset.OutputBase
      • org.apache.jena.sparql.resultset.TextOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OutputFormatter
    @Deprecated
public class TextOutput
extends OutputBase
    Deprecated.
    This will become an internal class. Use ResultSetFormatter.output(org.apache.jena.query.ResultSet, org.apache.jena.sparql.resultset.ResultsFormat) or ResultsWriter.create().lang(ResultSetLang.RS_Text).write(...)

    Takes a ResultSet object and creates displayable formatted output in plain text.

    Note: this is compute intensive and memory intensive. It needs to read all the results first (all the results are then in-memory) in order to find things the maximum width of a column value; then it needs to pass over the results again, turning them into output.

    See Also:
    for convenience ways to call this formatter
